  "Vectors can be factored out of scalar addition": "",
  "The distributive property c(u + v) = cu + cv states that scalar multiplication distributes over vector addition. This means multiplying a sum of vectors by a scalar is the same as multiplying each vector individually and then adding the results.": "",
